@startuml
title Viaverse Dispute / Refund / Payout — Activity Diagram
start
:Problem before payout;
:Open dispute;
:Validate job/payment state and participant;
if (Valid dispute?) then (yes)
  :Block payout;
  :Create payout hold;
  :Collect evidence\nmessages / media / notes;
  :Notify other party;
  :Wait for response or timeout;
  :Admin reviews evidence;
  if (Resolution decision?) then (refund)
    :Refund full/partial;
  elseif (payout)
    :Release payout;
  else (split)
    :Partial refund + partial payout;
  endif
  :Write audit log\nreason + actor;
  :Close dispute;
  :Update trust/risk and job/payment refs;
  :Emit resolution events;
else (no)
  :Reject / route to support;
endif
stop

note bottom
Dispute SLAs and timeouts should be configurable.
Timeout can auto-escalate, but money movement still requires policy decision and audit.
end note
@enduml
